  // Social: "If you've recently lost a spouse, you may be facing a wall of accounts, phones, passwords, and logins you don't know how to access. There is a path forward — and you do not have to walk it today. This is a gentle, step-by-step guide made with grief in mind."
  // Newsletter: "Few things in grief are as quietly overwhelming as the digital side of losing someone. Their phone keeps chiming. Subscriptions keep charging the credit card. You need a password you never knew. This guide was written to sit beside you through all of it — with no judgment, no rush, and no assumptions that you should already know how any of this works. We'll walk through what to do first, what can wait, how to get into their phone and email, how to notify banks and social media, and how to preserve the photos and memories before anything gets closed down. Take it at your pace. There is no deadline."
